   INTEL-TRIAL (Washington) _ At the heart of the government's
antitrust case that goes on trial against Intel Corp. on Tuesday is
a meeting nearly five-and-a-half years ago at the industry's annual
Comdex convention in Las Vegas. There, in November 1993, the
chairman of the giant chipmaker cut a fateful deal with his
counterpart at a small but leading maker of highly specialized
computer workstations, Intergraph Corp. By Stephen Labaton.
