   HDTV-INTERACTIVE (Washington) _ Results of a recent study by the
Consumer Electronics Manufacturers Association, the industry's main
trade group, showed that consumers are at least as interested in
using digital television sets for interactive services as for
watching high-definition programming. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   BUYING-ELECTRONICS (Undated) _ Buoyed by strong holiday sales of
large screen television sets, video cassette recorders and Sony
PlayStation video games, and signs pointing to strong first-quarter
sales, the makers and sellers of consumer electronics products are
predicting that 1999 could be the industry's best year ever. Rather
than scaring off consumers, they are counting on a dazzling _
skeptics might say dizzying _ array of new and enhanced products to
stimulate sales. By Sharon R. King.
