<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CONSUMERQ&AMP;A09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CONSUMER Q&AMP;A
 &HT;    By Jane Greig
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: There are Grammy Awards for record of the year, album of the
year and song of the year. What is the difference? _Becky A.
</P>
<P>
   A: The Grammys are presented by the National Academy of
Recording Arts &AMP; Sciences Inc. The song of the year is an award for
the songwriter; the record is for the song's performer and
producer; and the album is for the album's performer and producer.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What requirements are needed to join the Alaska State
Troopers? _David V.
</P>
<P>
   A: Want to earn more than $3,500 a month for recruit positions
in exotic stations such as Ketchikan or Sitka? Alaska State Trooper
recruits must meet the following minimum requirements: a high
school diploma or GED; at least 21 years old; a valid Alaska
driver's license; and residency in Alaska. In addition, recruits
must never have been convicted of a felony or domestic violence or
have two or more driving-while-intoxicated offenses in the past 10
years. A long list of other ``must have nots'' includes use of
marijuana during the past two years. Sound like a fit? Contact the
Alaska Department of Public Safety, P.O. Box 111200, Juneau, Alaska
99811-1200 or visit www.dps.state.ak.us. Q: I have two daughters
and would like to have a third child. I have heard that the odds of
my third child being another girl are 90 percent. The theory is a
woman's body can chemically favor the conception of one sex or
another. Is there any scientific evidence to support this theory?
_Amber S.
</P>
<P>
   A: Nope, declares John Ashkenas, deputy editor of the American
Journal of Human Genetics. ``Generally the odds are the same for
every birth, as they are independent events.'' Trends in the sex
ratio? The National Center for Health Statistics says the birth
ratio for the sexes has remained about the same for 50 years. Live
births: 1,050 boys for every 1,000 girls. (Who's going to tell Pat
Boone?
</P>
<P>
   Q: Please find out when Kate Spade will produce a line for the
males in this world. _ Lee Ullmann
</P>
<P>
   A: Good news for all you dandies. There is a new line by Kate
Spade, the woman's purse guru: the Jack Spade line. Jack, unlike
Kate, is a mythical person. For now, the best place to see the
entire Jack Spade line is the Soho Kate Spade store, 454 Broom St.,
New York. Select from Jack Spade messenger bags (a.k.a field bags),
weekend bags, raincoats, dopp kits, scarves and backpacks ranging
from $50 to $500.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I saw the ``Biography of Liberace'' on A&AMP;E recently. The
program mentioned a book that changed Liberace's life. Will you
please find out the name of that book, the author and where I can
find it?
</P>
<P>
   _ V.E. Walsh
</P>
<P>
   A: ``The Magic of Believing,'' by Claude Bristol, a self
help/motivational author whose mantra is you can achieve whatever
you desire. The nimble-fingered showman read the tome during a low
career period and it snapped him into action. To purchase a copy,
call the Liberace Museum at (702) 798-5595. Eighteen of the 39
pianos owned by the legendary Liberace are on display at the
museum, along with several elaborate costumes (eat your heart out,
Elton John).
</P>
<P>
   Q: My daughter is getting married in June in upstate New York _
a garden wedding and reception. We hope to buy white umbrellas for
the guests, to shield from rain or sun. Do you have a suggestion
where I could look for about 100 inexpensive, white umbrellas? _
Norma Lehmann
</P>
<P>
   A: Sounds like a great setting. Adnet (339-9695) will order 100
white, 42-inch umbrellas for the event for a mere $5 each (give
them seven working days' notice). Minimum order is 84 umbrellas. If
you want to add a monogram to the umbrella, they can do that, too.
Closer to the site of the wedding, a sleek, push-button, white
umbrella is available from Uncle Sam Umbrella Shop, 161 W. 57th
St., New York. Ask for Gilbert.
</P>
<P>
   Q: If someone changes a tip amount on a credit card, is this
considered a felony or a misdemeanor? He or she did not sign their
name to the card, nor has it been stolen. _D.K.
</P>
<P>
   A: Felony theft involves amounts $1,500 and over; misdemeanor
theft, under that amount. Mack Martinez, criminal trial chief of
the Travis County District Attorney's office, says unless the
thefts can be aggregated, it is misdemeanor theft. (I think a card
payer would notice a $1,500 tip.) To report such activity, call the
Austin Police Department at 356-4249.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I lost 10 U.S. Saving Bonds in the mail when I was
transferred from Oklahoma to Washington, D.C. How do I go about
recovering these bonds? They have reached their seven-year
maturity. _Norbert Flores
</P>
<P>
   A: Not to worry. Lost, stolen, mutilated or destroyed bonds can
be replaced free of charge if the Bureau of the Public Debt can
establish that the bonds have not been cashed. (Keep records of
bond serial numbers, issue dates, registration and Social Security
or taxpayer identification numbers in a safe place separate from
the bonds _ as you would with traveler's checks.) To replace these
bonds, complete Form PD F 1048 with whatever information you
remember, such as the approximate issue date, the complete names,
addresses, Social Security number that appeared on the bond and the
bond serial number. To obtain a form, ask for one at most
commercial banks or at www.savingsbonds.gov. Mail the completed
form to Bureau of the Public Debt, Parkersburg, WV 26106-1328.
Replacement bonds will still show the original issue date. If it is
discovered your bonds have been cashed, an investigation will
ensue. Q: Is there a law requiring apartment complexes to hold your
security deposit in escrow and have it be interest-bearing? Some
apartments have that policy and some don't. _Marie Pfau
</P>
<P>
   A: ``No, there is no requirement in Texas law that landlords
invest these funds and pay tenants the interest,'' says Austin
Tenants' Council spokesman Bruce Rodenborn, although many states do
have such laws. If you find an apartment complex with this policy,
it is a perk. The landlord is required to return your security
deposit within 30 days of move-out along with an itemized list of
deductions (if any). Of course, that is hard to do if you have not
provided the landlord with your forwarding address.
</P>
<P>
   Upshot/ Update/Uproar:
</P>
<P>
   _ Shirt look like you slept in it? Have an iron but no ironing
board? Ironing pads/blankets designed to sit on a bed, floor or
counter are available from the Lillian Vernon catalog at (800)
285-5555 or the Container Store.
</P>
<P>
   Contact Jane S. Greig at P.O. Box 670, Austin, Texas 78767;
(512) 445-3697; e-mail jgreig(at)statesman.com or fax (512)
445-3968.
</P>
<P>
   For copies of Jane's book, ``Thanks for Asking!'' _ a
compilation of more than 600 favorite questions and answers _ call
(800) 424-6291.
</P>
