<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Make friends around the world
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you're 8 to 16, Smithsonian Magazine's Kids' Castle
at http://www.kidscastle.si.edu/ is a site to see. It offers
articles and photographs about sports, history, the arts, travel,
science and space. Plus, kids can make friends from all over the
world through the online message boards. There are challenging
games and contests, including a concentration game. The site also
offers links to kids games on other sites.
</P>
<P>
   WHO'S GOT THE RIGHT STUFF?
</P>
<P>
   Want to follow all the action in the NCAA basketball tournament?
Head to today's sports section and locate the NCAA bracket. The
bracket is a large chart that lists all 64 teams that were selected
to play in this month-long series of games. You can use the bracket
in two ways: You can fill in the blanks as games happen to track
who's winning or you can try to predict ahead of time which teams
will do well. Either way, it's fun to see which team fights its way
to the top of the heap.
</P>
<P>
   RACE WITH THE BIG BOYS
</P>
<P>
   What could be better than a 53-foot big rig filled with a bunch
of NASCAR stuff? Home Depot's mobile NASCAR unit brings the store's
No. 20 show car, a racing simulator and an interactive tool
workshop to stores in the Atlanta area this week. All activities
are free. Catch the big rig from: 3 to 7 p.m. Wednesday in
Kennesaw; 3 to 7 p.m. Friday in Duluth; and 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.
Saturday in Marietta. Call stores for more information.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
