u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GOOFY-PHONE09-COX     03-08 0225
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOOFY-PHONE09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Goofy does everything except take messages
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Any old telephone can place a phone call, but how
many of them can snore?
</P>
<P>
   The Goofy Telephone is made in the shape of the Disney cartoon
character Goofy. And in addition to the normal phone functions, the
Goofy Telephone speaks five phrases in the character's voice and
has three animated motions.
</P>
<P>
   The head raises and lowers, the eyes open and close and the
stomach rises in falls in time to Goofy's snoring sounds.
</P>
<P>
   Each time the phone rings, the animated Goofy goes through a
series of sayings, including ``Did you hear somethin' ringing'?''
``Well, whaddaya know, a phone call!'' and ``If it's for me I'm
a-sleepin'.''
</P>
<P>
   The phone also has a switchable ringer, last number redial and a
demo button to make the phone perform its animated functions.
</P>
<P>
   The phone, which won an award for innovation at the
International Consumer Electronics Show in January, sells for
between $80 and $100, according to its manufacturer, Kash N Gold of
Ronkonkoma, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   The product is sold primarily by catalog and is available from
Service Merchandise, Sharper Image, Spencer Gifts, Fingerhut,
Spiegel and Teledynamics.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
