</P>
<P>
   containing an enigmatic letter, a divorced woman
</P>
<P>
   encounters love.
</P>
<P>
   BLACK AND BLUE, by Anna Quindlen. (Dell, $7.50.) ...... 4 .... 3
</P>
<P>
   After her husband turns violent, a woman flees to
</P>
<P>
   Florida with her son to start a new life.
</P>
<P>
   JEWEL, by Bret Lott. (Washington Square/Pocket, $14.) .. 5 .. 6
</P>
<P>
   The life of a poor Mississippi woman is strained
</P>
<P>
   and enriched by her daughter, who has Down syndrome.
</P>
