<DOCNO> NYT19990308.0201 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-08 13:46 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1858 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      03-08 0402
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`WHAT DREAMS' A WASTE; `BARRIO' THE REAL THING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``What Dreams May Come'' _ Robin Williams stars in
a treacly tale of life in the hereafter. Believe me, if it's filled
with the cotton-candy colors and unbearable aphorisms that populate
this moronic concoction, I'd just as soon accept Flannery
O'Connor's view (in ``Wise Blood'') that ``them's that dead stay
that way.'' Cuba Gooding Jr. is wasted in a throwaway role.
</P>
<P>
   ``Down for the Barrio'' _ This low-budget action picture has
some technical flaws and awkward dramatic sections, but the
realistic footage of LA street gang _ and the pure conviction of
the filmmakers _ more than makes up for its shortcomings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: ``Armageddon'' might not have rocked too many
critics' Top 10 lists, but it's become a favorite of the DVD set.
It tops the video sales list for the third week in a row. ``I shot
`Armageddon' with DVD in mind,'' director Michael Bay told Video
magazine. ``Because of my background in commercials, I've always
been aware of the degradation factor you get with broadcast and, to
a lesser extent, with film transfers. With DVD, you get none of
that. And the sound fidelity is unmatched.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 16: ``The Waterboy,'' ``Bulworth,''
``No Laughing Matter,'' ``Living Out Loud,'' ``One True Thing,''
``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul Monette: The Brink of Summer's End,''
``Who the Hell Is Juliette?'', ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit.''
March 23: ``Pleasantville,'' ``Mighty Joe Young,'' ``Firelight,''
``Bride of Chucky,'' ``Jerry Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``Carla's
Song,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn 2,'' ``Strike!'' March 30: ``The
Rugrats Movie,'' ``Oblomov,'' ``Siberiade,'' ``Home Fries,''
``Mutual Needs.'' April 6: ``Beloved,'' ``American History X,'' ``A
Soldier's Daughter Never Cries,'' ``I Still Know What You Did Last
Summer,'' ``An Unexpected Life,'' ``Meet Joe Black,'' ``The Dentist
2.'' April 13: ``The Tempest,'' ``Bug Buster,'' ``Ambushed,''
``Basil,'' ``Detroit 9000,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure.'' April
20: ``A Bug's Life,'' ``Monument Ave.,'' ``Simon Birch,'' ``Apt
Pupil,'' ``A Night at the Roxbury,'' April 27: ``Happiness,''
``Ground Control,'' May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the City.'' May 11:
``Another Day in Paradise.''
</P>
