   SWEEPSTAKES-SENATE (Washington) _ An elderly man tells the
Senate he spent thousands of dollars on magazine subscriptions
because he thought it would boost his chances of winning millions
in sweepstakes contests. Sens. Susan Collins, R-Maine and Carl
Levin, D-Mich., are pushing legislation that would require
sweepstakes companies to stop promoting such practices. By JENNIFER
CORBETT DOOREN.
