<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Leaders of the major religious right
organizations are cranky these days, unable to agree on a suitable
Republican presidential nominee and angry that the GOP-controlled
Congress has not met their demands on social issues. They are even
talking about picking up their marbles and going home from the GOP
game. The Republicans should get so lucky. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
