<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mindspring to offer high speed hookups in Southeast
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ MindSpring Enterprises, the Atlanta-based Internet
service provider, entered the world of high speed Internet access
Monday by offering service over cable television modems.
</P>
<P>
   MindSpring said its ``Fast Access'' cable modem service is now
available in in Montgomery, Ala. The company also plans to offer
cable modem service in Augusta, Fla., Charleston, S.C., Columbus,
Ga. and Panama City, Fla. in the near future. Cable modem service
allows users to access the Internet at speeds up to 50 times faster
than standard dial-up phone connections.
</P>
<P>
   Knology offers interactive video, voice and data services to
mid-sized cities in the Southeast. MindSpring and Knology are
sister companies orignally funded by the same company, ITC Holdings
of West Point, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   The service costs $39.95 per month with a one-time installation
fee of $149.95, which includes installation of all equipment and
service. The cable modem is available for lease at $13 per month.
</P>
<P>
   Frances Katz writes for The Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
