<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Tuesday, March 9. If you
have
<TEXT>
<P>
   any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
CHARTER SCHOOLS (Phoenix) - The third and final installment of our
charter-school series, looking at what is _ and what should be _ on
the horizon on the movement. By KELLY PEARCE. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
JOE (Phoenix) - The late Joe Dimaggio was not only a great baseball
player, but managed to project an image of decency and civility. He
may have been Mr. Coffee to a younger generation, but to anyone old
enough to remember, he was the very definition of ``class.'' By
RICHARD NILSEN. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - The longest unbroken streak by a
professional athlete in any sport ended quietly Monday. After 84
years, 3 months, 1 weeks and 4 days of uninterrupted dignity, the
great Joe DiMaggio died. I've marked time by DiMaggio all my life.
I was born Nov. 25, 1954, the day DiMaggio turned 40. By E.J.
MONTINI.
</P>
<P>
   Story moved in the ``S'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
ALLIED-WASTE (Scottsdale, Ariz.) - Allied Waste Industries, a
Scottsdale garbage company whose Harley-riding executives have been
on a nonstop buying spree, bagged its biggest deal yet Monday when
it announced a $10 billion acquisition of larger rival
Browning-Ferris Industries. The combined company, which will have
its headquarters in Scottsdale, will be the second largest garbage
company in the country and Arizona's largest public company by a
long shot. With $6.6 billion in annual sales, it also likely will
become Arizona's fourth Fortune 500 company. By DAWN GILBERTSON.
Story will move in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GARBAGE (Phoenix) - Overview of trash business and what latest deal
means. By RUSS WILES. Story will move int he ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
