automakers began adopting lean manufacturing techniques, the
aerospace industry is embracing the concept to cut costs.
Executives are now bandying about Japanese terms like kaizen
(continuous improvement) and kanban (the just-in-time system). They
often mispronounce them horribly, but are applying them well enough
to achieve some startling efficiency gains in an industry long
known for high costs and wasteful procedures. By Andrew Pollack.
