mound. DiMaggio died early Monday morning after a battle with lung
cancer and pneumonia. (Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- March 8, 1999 -- OBIT-DIMAGGIO-2, 03-08 --
Joe DiMaggio walks out onto the diamond at Yankee Stadium to
deliver the first pitch against the Oakland A's in April of 1998.
DiMaggio, who played 13 season with the Yankees, had been battling
lung cancer since October. He died early Monday morning. (G. Paul
Burnett/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- March 8, 1999 -- OBIT-DIMAGGIO-1, 03-08 --
Former Yankee, Joe DiMaggio, acknowledges the crowd at Yankee
Stadium after throwing the first pitch of the last day of the 1998
season. DiMaggio, who underwent lung cancer surgery in October and
had been battling its complications, died early Monday morning. He
was 84. (Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
