<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURY CLOUDS TRADE TALK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Would the Lakers really trade Eddie Jones to
Charlotte for damaged goods? That's the question Lakers officials
themselves will be pondering between now and the NBA's 3 p.m.
Thursday trade deadline.
</P>
<P>
   It's been reported that Jones and Elden Campbell would be
swapped for Glen Rice, J.R. Reid and B.J. Armstrong. It's even been
called a done deal by several media outlets.
</P>
<P>
   But Rice himself raised serious doubts about the deal this
weekend, when he said he can't fully extend his right (shooting)
arm, seven weeks after surgery on his elbow. In an interview with
the Charlotte Observer, published Monday, a frustrated Rice said he
doesn't know when he'll be able to play again.
</P>
<P>
   ``Is it a week? Is it a month? I don't know,'' he said. ``I
don't think it's anything like a month, though. Just do something
and put me out of my misery if it's a month.''
</P>
<P>
   According to the Observer, the teams are still discussing the
trade.
</P>
<P>
   Rice, 31, one of the league's top pure shooters, had
arthroscopic surgery Jan. 22 to remove loose particles in his
elbow. He is rehabilitating at his Miami home and continues to feel
intermittent pain, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers have won seven straight games, including Sunday's
impressive victory over the Jazz in Utah, but management believes
the addition of a 3-point shooting ace would solidify their bid for
an NBA championship. Rice has averaged 44.4 percent from beyond the
arc the past three seasons, including a league-leading 47 percent
in 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers also have been eager to unload Campbell's $7
million-a-year contract, which runs through 2003. If they make the
trade, the Lakers will have turned over four-fifths of the starting
lineup that finished the 1997-98 season.
</P>
<P>
   Shaquille O'Neal would be the only holdover. Travis Knight has
replaced Robert Horry (power forward), Derek Harper has replaced
Derek Fisher (point guard) and Kobe Bryant has replaced Rick Fox
(small forward). Rice would become the new small forward, with
Bryant shifting to Jones' vacated shooting guard slot.
</P>
<P>
   __ Jones watch: Jones, who last week was joking with reporters
about the trade, saying mock good-byes, has been noticeably quiet
the past few days and appears more bothered than ever about it. He
scored just five points in Sunday's win.
</P>
<P>
   Magic Johnson came to Monday's practice and offered Jones some
encouraging words. Johnson also spent 30 minutes working with
Bryant on his post-up game, and afterward said he would be more
involved in the post-Del Harris era.
</P>
<P>
   ``There was an unwritten rule that I couldn't be around,''
Johnson said. ``I'm back now.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Worm watch: Dennis Rodman skipped Monday's practice at
Southwest College, but his absence was prearranged and excused,
according to the team. Rodman was said to be taking care of
``personal business.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
