<SLUG> BC-BY-DESIGN-FASHION-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FILLIPS, FROM CURLS TO COLOR 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A roundup of styling trends seen so far on the runways in New
York and Milan, Italy:
</P>
<P>
   It may be just a straw in the wind, or else the first sign of a
change of direction for hair, but curls are back. They appeared on
several runways for fall, including that of Versace, which
abandoned last season's '70s-straight dos for flyaway curls on
models.
</P>
<P>
   Belts, too. They might be leather thongs tied at the waist or
under the bosom, or wide bands of leather or fabric slung around
the hips. For fall, low-riding skirts and pants have been the rule,
but even slinky dresses are often shown with hip belts.
</P>
<P>
   With skirts from micro-mini to floor-sweeping, boots are making
a strong showing, especially midcalf high with flat or chunky high
heels.
</P>
<P>
   And the trendy color is orange, in shades from pale to strong.
But it's not to be worn with black, except on Halloween. It goes
with browns and earth tones.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
